headline: Better Telecom Stock: AT&T vs. Verizon
summary: Amid recent stock market volatility, the telecom sector offers some respite.  Telecom stocks are relatively stable because of the ubiquity and importance of mobile devices in society, allowing telecoms to produce reliable revenue and free cash flow (FCF).  As a testament to this, while many stocks plunged in the past few weeks, shares of telecom giant AT&T (NYSE: T) hit a 52-week high of $29.03 in April, while rival Verizon Communications (NYSE: VZ) reached its high of $47.35 in March.
